JOHANNESBURG - Investigations by overseas-based entities into the Gupta family's business dealings are increasing.
	
	Business Day is reporting that Dubai's Central Bank is looking into alleged money laundering by the controversial family. It's alleged that it's using shelf companies for the money laundering. READ: Guptas laundered R760m through fake Dubai companies: report The President of the Dubai Chamber of Commerce and Industry says the allegations are being discussed at the highest level. It represents the business interests of over 200,000 companies. At the same time, the UK is asking the European Parliament to review its laws regarding money laundering amid the allegations. eNCA